<div class="sub-content-header">Foursquare at the 2011 International CES: Turn Your Badge into Prizes</div>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i><span class="smallText">Dec 29, 2010 04:00:04</span></i>

<br /><br />

Check in, explore, find your friends and win at the 2011 CES!&nbsp; Follow the International CES on Foursquare at <A href="http://foursquare.com/intlces" target=_blank>http://foursquare.com/intlces</A>&nbsp; for tips and tricks to get around this year’s show. Check in at&nbsp;five of the 10 official CES venues between Tuesday, January 4 and Sunday, January 9 to earn the official, coveted 2011 CES Foursquare badge.<BR><BR>For CES 2011, the CEA and Foursquare have teamed up to turn your badge into a chance to win prizes and giveaways.&nbsp;Once you earn your official 2011 CES Foursquare badge, stop by the Experience CEA booth in Central Hall to get your official 2011 CES Foursquare button (the first 2,000). Plus, you’ll be entered in a Grand Prize drawing - two lucky badge holders will win a ‘House Full of Music’ courtesy of Sonos. <BR><BR><A href="/docs/FoursquareAtCESOfficialRules.pdf" target=_blank>Read the official rules.<BR></A><BR><STRONG>2011 CES Check-In Locations </STRONG>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>2011 International CES </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES Experience CEA, LVCC, Grand Lobby </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES, LVCC, North Hall </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES, LVCC, Central Hall </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES, LVCC, South Hall </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES, Las Vegas Hilton </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES, High Performance Audio at The Venetian </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES Press Day (Wednesday, January 5, 8:00 am – 5:45 p.m. at Venetian) </LI>
<LI class=text>2011 CES Research Day (Wednesday, January 5, 1:00 pm&nbsp; – 5:00 pm LVCC) </LI>
<LI class=text>Official CES Tweetup, Las Vegas Hilton (Friday, January 7, 4:00 – 7:00 pm)</LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>Go Beyond the Badge <BR></STRONG>Ever wished you could leave CES with at least one of the cool products you see on the show floor? With your 2011 CES Foursquare badge you can!&nbsp; Stop by the following booths and show your badge to unlock the following opportunities: </P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>All 2011 CES Badge holders who visit the Livio Radio booth can flash their badge to receive a CES survival item. Follow them @Livioradio and <A href="http://foursquare.com/livioradio">http://foursquare.com/livioradio</A>.</LI>
<LI class=text>Show your badge at the Sharp booth for the opportunity to enter their daily giveaway. Each day of CES, one lucky badge holder will win either a Sharp sound bar, Blu-ray player, iPod docking station or 32” AQUOS LCD TV. One badge holder will win their grand prize, a 52” AQUOS Quattron LCD TV.&nbsp; Follow them @Sharp_USA.</LI>
<LI class=text>The first 200 people to show their 2011 CES Badge at the SanDisk booth will receive a SanDisk slotRadio Card. Follow them @Sandisk. </LI>
<LI class=text>Sonos will be giving away two Sonos multi-room music systems to fill you home music. Enter for your chance to win at the Experience CEA booth.&nbsp; Follow them @Sonos and <A href="http://foursquare.com/sonos">http://foursquare.com/sonos</A>.</LI>
<LI class=text>Check into the Intel booth and complete a challenge for a chance to win a new Intel Core laptop. Follow Intel on Foursquare http://foursquare.com/intel and Twitter @intel <A href="http://twitter.com/intel" target=_blank>http://twitter.com/intel</A>. Snap a photo of your favorite part of the Intel booth and post to Twitter and Foursquare using the hashtags #CES and #VisualLife. </LI></UL>
