<div class="sub-content-header">Social Media Expands CES</div>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i><span class="smallText">Dec 20, 2010 01:04:51</span></i>

<br /><br />

<A href="http://www.nxtbook.com/nxtbooks/cea/vision1110/#/0"><EM>Taken from the November/December 2010 issue of CE Vision Magazine<BR></EM></A><BR>Tradeshows are primarily about bringing people face-to-face to network and conduct business. Social networking tools can help make this happen by better connecting people. <BR><BR>For the past several years, <A href="http://www.CESweb.org">the International CES </A>has been a leading user of social media tools to promote the tradeshow, its exhibitors and all the amazing events and product launches. This includes utilizing social media and location-based marketing tools like mobile apps, the <A href="http://blog.ce.org/">CEA blog – Digital Dialogue</A>, <A href="http://CESweb.org/twitter">Twitter</A> and <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/facebook">Facebook</A>, to reach attendees and exhibitors, before, during and after the show. <BR><BR>More than 10,000 industry professionals <A href="http://blog.ce.org/" target=_blank>visit CEA’s Digital Dialogue</A> each month leading up to the International CES to learn about the latest product trends expected on the show floor.&nbsp; Additionally, the CEA and CES Facebook pages connect people throughout the year and provide the latest news. And while CEA uses Twitter to reach CES attendees, it isn’t the only one who thinks the International CES is worth tweeting about – at the end of the first day of the 2010 International CES, there were 25,000 tweets referencing <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/twitter">#CES on Twitter.<BR></A><BR>These social media tools help to make navigating the 2011 International CES show floor as easy as possible. For the upcoming show, CEA is partnering with Core-Apps to produce a new mobile app.&nbsp; <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/followme">The Follow Me app</A> allows CES attendees to link to their friends’ CES schedules, provides interactive floor maps with routing to booths, and allows for social media and downloading exhibitor information directly from mobile devices.<BR><BR>Follow Me is free and has a native app for Apple, BlackBerry and Android devices, in addition to the Follow Me Web app for other Internet-ready phones.&nbsp; <BR><BR>Through social media, CES attendees and exhibitors can learn about the show with the touch of a button. To join the CES digital conversation, <A href="http://www.CESweb.org">visit CESweb.org</A>, follow it on <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/twitter">Twitter at intlCES</A>, check out <A href="http://blog.ce.org/">CEA’s Digital Dialogue</A> or visit the <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/facebook">International CES’s Facebook page</A>.<BR><BR><A href="http://www.nxtbook.com/nxtbooks/cea/vision1110/#/0">Read more stories like this&nbsp;from the most recent edition of <EM>CE Vision Magazine</EM>.</A>
<br><br>
